line_1: How fierce his Jav'lin o'er the trembling Lakes
Are hurry'd down the dreadful lakes;
line_2: And all her ducks, and all her drakes,

line_1: Curls her deep wells, and rimples all her lakes,
line_2: Her wrinkling founts with soft vibration shakes,

line_1: O'er Earth's green lap, or shoots amid her lakes,
line_2: SYLPHS! from each sun-bright leaf, that twinkling shakes

line_1: Marks the wide ruins, and the sulphur'd lakes;
line_2: — Oft the lone Pilgrim, that his road forsakes,

line_1: To Form new Mines beneath the Oazy Lakes,
line_2: The flaming Oar down to its Center makes,

line_1: Or plunge him deep in blue sulphureous lakes;
line_2: Or lash his quivering flesh with twisted snakes;
